comments.body:
@hectorcorrea I'm quoting what you wrote `This code also takes into consideration the "Oversize" token that Alma puts at the front of some call numbers.` We decided to put $k (that may include Oversize) in front of the call_number_display not Alma. See call_number_display: 
https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/blob/5c1f6ed3f4b2a20bb98c8e72ddbbdf3519cf257e/marc_to_solr/lib/traject_config.rb#L1307 vs call_number_browse_s: https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/blob/5c1f6ed3f4b2a20bb98c8e72ddbbdf3519cf257e/marc_to_solr/lib/traject_config.rb#L1315 where we keep $k at the end of the call_number_browse_s.

@christinach @hackartisan I made a few adjustments per your review. In particular I narrowed the location check for "firestore$stacks" and made the code to adjust the call number a bit more generic and easier to expand to take other prefixes into consideration if we need to.

Notice that I am adjusting the call number *in place* rather than pulling the values from Solr. I am not totally pleased with this approach, I think it duplicates the logic from Traject, but, I am afraid that for records with more than one call number (e.g. https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/722287) I won't be able to match the values in Alma to the ones in Solr to pick the right sortable number. We can discuss this if we really want to use the Solr values.
Oh yeah, I also need to add tests, but I am waiting to see if this is even the approach we want to take :)
Added tests.
